data.description:
Eco-friendly Haven on 4.59 Acres with a Sprawling Shop
Welcome to this upgraded gem, nestled amidst sprawling acreages and farm land, just minutes from the bustling heart of Downtown Crescent and Guthrie. This home is situated on a sizeable 4.59-acre plot, promising serenity and space.
The main dwelling is a beautifully upgraded 3-bedroom, 2-bath home that offers an inside laundry, two dining spaces, an additional living space perfect for an office or hobby room, and an enclosed patio. The double-pane windows flood the home with natural light, providing stunning views of the surrounding landscape.
Since its purchase in 2020, this home has seen numerous eco-conscious upgrades. A state-of-the-art solar system consisting of 50 panels ensures sustainable energy consumption and lower utility bills. Upgraded to a 600-amp electrical service, this property caters to modern demands without compromising on environmental responsibility. A 50-amp RV outlet has been added to the north side of the house, perfect for adventurous homeowners.
But the appeal doesn't end there. The property also boasts a 40x60 shop with power, two large doors, and 12'6" tall walls. The metal roll-up door is 16' wide and 12' tall, with sliding barn doors that are 19'6" wide and 11'6" tall. Since 2020, the shop has seen significant upgrades, including electrical wiring throughout the overhead area, a new water faucet, several mini splits for air control, and spray foam insulation.
Other remarkable features include a sprinkler system, two storm shelters, a concrete drive to the 2-car garage, central heat and air, a roof installed in 2016, a GE Generator, and a reverse osmosis system.
This property is not merely a home, but a lifestyle that seamlessly blends modern convenience, eco-conscious living, and the tranquility of rural life. Don't miss out on this unique opportunity.
